<https://example.org/arpo> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Ontology> .
<https://example.org/arpo> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionIRI> <https://example.org/arpo/2.0> .
<https://example.org/arpo> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/creator> "Fırat Kaya Özgenç" .
<https://example.org/arpo> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/date> "2026-05-05" .
<https://example.org/arpo> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "A formal OWL 2 DL ontology for representing academic research publications, authors, venues, institutions, citation relationships, funding, and open access status." .
<https://example.org/arpo> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/license> <https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/> .
<https://example.org/arpo> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "Academic Research Publication Ontology (ARPO)" .
<https://example.org/arpo> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#priorVersion> <https://example.org/arpo/1.0> .
<https://example.org/arpo> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#changeNote> "v2.0: Added ResearchGroup, Grant, FundingBody, AffiliationRecord, OpenAccessStatus, PeerReviewRecord, Preprint classes. Added 6 new object properties and 4 new data properties. Modelling follows MOMo methodology with record and controlled-vocabulary patterns." .
